if ($aa==$bb){$aa++;}
$b3 = $bb**3;

TEXT(beginproblem());
BEGIN_TEXT
Find the particular solution of the differential equation
\[\frac{dy}{dx} = (x-$aa)e^{-2y}\]
satisfying the initial condition \(y($aa)=\ln($aa)\).
$BR
Answer: \(y\)=  \{ ans_rule(45)\}
$BR
Your answer should be a function of \(x\).
$PAR

END_TEXT

